  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25000 from their employer. However, as a judge, I must weigh mitigating factors such as the defendant having no prior criminal record and having already made partial restitution. The outburst from the spectator demanding a 10-year sentence is emotional and holds no legal bearing on this court. Considering the nature of white-collar crime, the first-time offense, and the defendant's willingness to make restitution, a relatively short period of incarceration is sufficient to serve as probation and deterrence.",
  "verdict": 12
